Class SegaServerObject

  • java.lang.Object
    • helpers.SegaServerObject
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public class SegaServerObject
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable
    This helper class is used to store info returned from a SQL database containing valid servers. The server can be for RBNB, MySQL, or any other SEGA related data store. These objects are used to provide valid server locations for the web users. The original implementation used serverIp to connect, but a safer alternative is to use the serverName field (e.g. romer.cefns.nau.edu:333 instead of 134.114.xx.xx)
    Author:
    jdk85
    See Also:
    SegaDataRequestFormServlet, Serialized Form
